  "openapi": "3.1.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "Career Talk API",
    "version": "0.0.1",
    "description": "REST API for **Career Talk** \u2014 a language-learning platform (Cambly-like) that connects tutors and students.\n\n## Getting started\n\nAll endpoints are served under the `/api` prefix. Use **Try it** on any operation to send requests from this page.\n\n1. **Register** (`POST /auth/register`) or **login** (`POST /auth/login`) to obtain an `access_token`.\n2. Click **Authorize** and paste: `Bearer {your_token}`.\n3. Call protected routes (users, profile, session management).\n\n## Authentication\n\nProtected routes require a **Laravel Sanctum** personal access token sent as a Bearer token:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}\n```\n\nPublic routes (register, login, forgot/reset password) do not require a token.\n\n| Action | Endpoint |\n| --- | --- |\n| Register (always creates a `student` account) | `POST /auth/register` |\n| Login | `POST /auth/login` |\n| Current user | `GET /auth/me` |\n| Refresh token (revokes the current one) | `POST /auth/refresh` |\n| Logout | `DELETE /auth/logout` |\n\n## Response format\n\nSuccessful responses use a consistent envelope:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {},\n  \"message\": null\n}\n```\n\n- `data` \u2014 payload (user, token, collection, etc.); omitted when empty.\n- `message` \u2014 optional human-readable string (e.g. password reset confirmation).\n\nPaginated lists (`GET /users`) return `data`, `links`, and `meta` inside the success payload.\n\n## Roles & authorization\n\nEach user has one role: `master`, `admin`, `tutor`, or `student`.\n\n- **master** / **admin** \u2014 full user management (list, create, update, delete).\n- **tutor** / **student** \u2014 can view and update only their own profile; cannot delete themselves.\n- Public registration and admin-created users always default to **student**; `role` cannot be set via the API.\n\n## Rate limiting\n\nAuth endpoints are throttled per IP or email+IP:\n\n| Endpoint | Limit |\n| --- | --- |\n| Login | 5 / minute (per email + IP) |\n| Register | 3 / minute (per IP) |\n| Forgot password | 3 / minute (per IP) |\n| Reset password | 5 / minute (per IP) |\n\nExceeded limits return **HTTP 429**.\n\n## Errors\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| `401` | Missing or invalid token |\n| `403` | Authenticated but not allowed |\n| `404` | Resource not found |\n| `422` | Validation failed (`message` + field errors) |\n| `429` | Too many requests |\n\nPassword-reset and forgot-password flows never reveal whether an email exists in the system."
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "http://localhost/api"
    }
  ],
  "tags": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Registration, login, password reset, and session management. Public routes issue Sanctum tokens; protected routes require a valid Bearer token."
    },
    {
      "name": "Users",
      "description": "User CRUD with role-based access. Admins and masters manage all users; tutors and students can only access their own record. All routes require authentication."
    }
  ],
  "security": [
    {
      "http": []
    }
  ],
